    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines the Compressed Routing Header (CRH). The CRH, like any other Routing header, contains a list of segment identifiers (SID). The CRH differs from other Routing headers in that its segment identifiers can be 8, 16 or 32 bits long.</t>
